# 1. Used Logistic Regression: Extremely low computational overhead (O(n_features * n_samples)) compared to Random Forest/Gradient Boosting.
# 2. Energy-efficient Preprocessing: SimpleImputer (median/mode) and StandardScaler are O(n) operations with very low memory footprint.
# 3. CPU Optimization: n_jobs=1 used to prevent excessive context switching on small datasets; lbfgs solver is memory-efficient.
# 4. Data Robustness: Implemented multi-separator parsing and header normalization to prevent runtime crashes.
